		<geography>
			<locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction location="CN">
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="en">This study performs a life-cycle assessment for a photovoltaic (PV) system with multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) modules in China</descriptionOfRestrictions>
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="zh">本研究对中国采用多晶硅组件的光伏系统进行了生命周期评估</descriptionOfRestrictions>
			</locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction>
		</geography>
		<technology>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) wafer slicing process using multi wire saw is intended for the production of solar-grade wafers for use in photovoltaic (PV) systems. These wafers are the foundation for creating multi-Si ingots, cells, and modules that are essential components in the assembly of PV panels designed to convert sunlight into electrical energy. This technology is predominantly utilized for the manufacture of multi-Si PV modules within the Chinese PV industry, contributing to its sustainable development.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">多丝锯切割多晶硅片的工艺旨在生产用于光伏系统的太阳能级硅片。这些硅片是创建多晶硅锭、电池和模块的基础 ，这些建组件是组装旨在将太阳光转换成电能的光伏板的关键组成部分。这项技术主要用于中国光伏产业多晶硅光伏组件的制造，有助于其可持续发展。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="7506d463-2654-e8c5-5be0-f5ac10ac3546" uri="../sources/7506d463-2654-e8c5-5be0-f5ac10ac3546.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">GSvEbT284otn6Uxk366cUzLpnKe.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
	</processInformation>
